{"id_resto": "g1637597-d18190867", "id_comment": "g1637597-d18190867-r737589151", "resto": "Istanbul_Grill", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1637597-d18190867-Reviews-Istanbul_Grill-Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Lovely Evening", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "7 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Moonlighter07", "reviewer_origin": ["Greater London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "49"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "43"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1637597-d18190867-r737589151-Istanbul_Grill-Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["We went to the Istanbul last night - my wife and two children. The decor is really nice and modern and the welcome we got by the waitress was very friendly. We got there early - 7pm, and by the time we left there were probably about 20 customers there, which is great for a Monday night just after Christmas. So, there was a nice buzz about the place. ", "We had a starter each, calamari, whitebait and holloumi which were all very nice. One of our main courses was the mixed grill for two. The portions were massive and we could only eat half of it. The salads were well prepared and fresh. When we asked to swap the rice for chips, it was no problem at all. The service from our waitress, Emily, was absolutely excellent. She was always highly attentive, professional and really friendly. The children loved her. She's a real asset to the place.", "All in all our first visit to this new restaurant was a big hit. We will definitely be returning."]}
{"id_resto": "g1637597-d18190867", "id_comment": "g1637597-d18190867-r738939302", "resto": "Istanbul_Grill", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1637597-d18190867-Reviews-Istanbul_Grill-Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Poor customer service, good food", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "13 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "RobbieG232", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1637597-d18190867-r738939302-Istanbul_Grill-Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["First of all, the food was good - no complaints about that. But the service from the staff was poor; I'd booked in advance a couple of hours before but they seemed to have lost this and I was made to feel awkward standing in the doorway while they worked it out. I was then given the wrong dish and I questioned this when it arrived but was reassured that I'd not be charged for it so I kept the meal (about \u00a33 difference, nothing major, it was the principle that I'd ended up with the wrong dish). When the bill came, the full cost had been charged and when I questioned this, I was made to feel like a liar as they said they believed the waitress had taken the correct order. When I said the amount was small, that I was the customer and how they were making me feel, plus the fact the wrong drinks had been given to us earlier in the evening, I expected them to show good customer service and apologise....but oh no! The waitress insisted that I must have made a mistake and that she'd have to check with the manager (all this for \u00a33!) and then proceeded to sit down with the manager at a table near us having a discussion for more than 2 minutes. All the time I was sitting there with my coat on, feeling very awkward in front of others. Eventually I got a revised bill, but there was no apology at any stage. No common sense, no customer service. All over \u00a33. They've lost a local customer and I won't be recommending them to anyone because of how they dealt with this and how they made us feel."]}
