{"id_resto": "g1646063-d1946997", "id_comment": "g1646063-d1946997-r744608050", "resto": "B_K_Salt_Beef_Bar", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1646063-d1946997-Reviews-B_K_Salt_Beef_Bar-Edgware_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Classic Jewish Brilliance", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "12 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Ian-Levine", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "7"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "24"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1646063-d1946997-r744608050-B_K_Salt_Beef_Bar-Edgware_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["A couple of years ago, I went to this restaurant's sister Deli restaurant, in Hatch End, with my late Mother and she thoroughly raved about it. Trying to find it again, I asked around but people mistakenly told me that it was closed, but nevertheless today I went to the main Edgware Restaurant with two of my cousins and we were in awe of the traditional quality of the spectacular food. Although not strictly kosher, it epitomises classic traditional old fashioned Jewish cuisine, Whereas most other Jewish restaurants these days tend to do middle eastern type food rather than timeless dishes like these. Since Blooms closed down, there is nowhere to go for decent chicken soup and matzoh balls, kreplach, chopped liver, hot salt beef, tongue, viennas, and all the classic vintage Hebrew delights that I so loved while growing up. This wonderful restaurant run by John and his sister in law, Gina brings back the taste of my youth, the fondly remembered delicacies of yester year.. Everything is perfect, the incredible service dished up with warmth and charisma, the taste of the food, which dances a tango on your taste buds, the best salt beef outside of the Stage Deli in New York. Blooms was never perfect and its memory pales into insignificance when compared to this truly rare find. Whatever else do do, try the hot salt beef sanwich - WOW - indescribable. It fills me with joy that such a restaurant like this can still exist in 2020."]}
