{"id_resto": "g1439404-d16870239", "id_comment": "g1439404-d16870239-r747594094", "resto": "Il_Vesuvio_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1439404-d16870239-Reviews-Il_Vesuvio_Restaurant-Bexleyheath_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Sunday Family Lunch ", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "25 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "ToniMurphy", "reviewer_origin": ["Milton Keynes, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "128"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "39"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1439404-d16870239-r747594094-Il_Vesuvio_Restaurant-Bexleyheath_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Visited on Sunday with my fiance, my dad and his girlfriend. What a lovely afternoon we had. Restaurant had a nice atmosphere for a Sunday afternoon and was very relaxed. Service was brilliant too. For starters the table had, mussels marinara, calamari, insalata tricolore and the meatballs. Great portion sizes and lovely flavours. Mains we went for margherita, mushroom risotto and x2 chicken parmigiana (in place of veal). The chefs were happy to change the option to chicken and the chicken escalopes were HUGE! Again, yummy mains too! Tasty and authentic! Dessert, we had profiteroles and x3 tirimisus and some espressos. Absolutely gorgeous. We spent ages here and were not rushed at all. We were even provided with a limoncello on the house, treat or what! Cant wait to come back! "]}
