{"id_resto": "g186338-d719657", "id_comment": "g186338-d719657-r745172080", "resto": "La_Trompette", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d719657-Reviews-La_Trompette-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Fabulous - perfect intimate space and great food/service", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "15 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Ben B", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "4"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d719657-r745172080-La_Trompette-London_England.html", "content": ["My wife and I spend Valentines lunch at this highly respected French style restaurant. Expect to be treated with great aplomb here. Almost as many staff as customers - and the restaurant was full but didn\u2019t feel crowded. No silly valentines \u201cideas\u201d were on show - just the sheer confidence that we would have an enjoyable lunch as a result of the great food and service. ", "The interior is smart but simple - warm but not cluttered. This restaurant is about the food, and your comfort. ", "The menu is daringly different - you won\u2019t find steak and chips on it. I had an interesting and delicious leek soup followed by a lamb dish that was cooked to perfection. My wife had Cornish squid which was amazing. ", "They accommodated (in advance) my wife\u2019s wheat intolerance with grace and respect - no huffing and puffing that we often experience around this important food allergy requirement. A specially made \u201cgift\u201d of a deep fried Parmesan foamed \u201cslice\u201d was given as an alternative to a slice of bread - along with gluten free toast too. ", "I had a slight issue with my non-alcoholic drink choice - I just didn\u2019t like it - and this was graciously swept away and replaced, following a detailed consultation with myself, with a bespoke improvised strawberry and rosemary concoction that more than made up for my initial problem. ", "This tells me that this restaurant knows it is only as good as it\u2019s last serving and is not resting on its laurels. The cheese board was demonstrated by an intensely knowledgable fellow who knew the progeny and construction of every item he had to offer. All of which were both delicious and impossible to find on the normal high street. ", " If that wasn\u2019t enough - the prices were actually reasonable. It\u2019s not a heap restaurant obviously, but the prices were honest and manageable, not stratospheric self aggrandising prices that some tip end restaurants feel they deserve. ", "Awesome. ", "B"]}
