{"id_resto": "g191301-d1014985", "id_comment": "g191301-d1014985-r744553723", "resto": "Chez_Lindsay", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g191301-d1014985-Reviews-Chez_Lindsay-Richmond_upon_Thames_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Brittany fine food, cosy atmosphere, unpretentious", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "12 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "127Fred", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "298"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "130"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "30", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g191301-d1014985-r744553723-Chez_Lindsay-Richmond_upon_Thames_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["In this restaurant with a view at the river, the atmosphere can be nice at times (a quiet lunchtime on a dark winter day is not the best bet, though).", "Staff management, and hence service, is no stuff for management books, with a lot of inefficiencies, strange allocation of responsibilities, etc. However, we did not notice any significant mishap, bad attitude or other visible impacts on service. We would like to see what happens when the place works at full capacity.", "This place serves in fact Brittany food (the place has not been French, officially until 1491, politically until much later, linguistically until, say, 1919, culturally until now, gastronomically until, say, quite recently). However, this fact is communicated with more discretion and subtlety than anticipated. We may see this as a missed opportunity to show something more unique.", "The surprise comes from the food, carefully and tastefully prepared, and a menu in quite an affordable price range."]}
{"id_resto": "g191301-d1014985", "id_comment": "g191301-d1014985-r745235402", "resto": "Chez_Lindsay", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g191301-d1014985-Reviews-Chez_Lindsay-Richmond_upon_Thames_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Excellent night at Chez Lindsay", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "15 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Anthonykking", "reviewer_origin": ["Bedford, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "22"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g191301-d1014985-r745235402-Chez_Lindsay-Richmond_upon_Thames_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["I took my partner here for a Valentine Day dinner and was very impressed, It's a very intimate and elegant restaurant with excellent service. My partner had the Moules \u00e0 la St Malo followed by Foie de Veau, Petits Pois \u00e0 la Fran\u00e7aise and I had Salade de Fruits de Mer with a main course of Croupe d\u2019Agneau. To accompany it we chose a bottle of ", "Ch\u00e2teau de Beaupr\u00e9. The Mussels were beautifully cooked and my only suggestion would be for the restaurant to source a slightly crustier baguette to accompany it. The mixed seafood and lamb were exquisite and the Semillion went well. We would heartedly recommend Chez Lindsay as a wonderful venue for dinner and will certainly come back here again to sample other dishes on the very extensive menu!"]}
