{"id_resto": "g528819-d9974263", "id_comment": "g528819-d9974263-r733228902", "resto": "Little_Mumbai", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g528819-d9974263-Reviews-Little_Mumbai-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Nice Twickenham restaurant", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "17 December 2019", "answer_text": ["Dear Sandra, thank you for your review and we are sorry you felt that way. But by no means we show any preference to certain customers. We serve each customer as they come and serve their orders in the same sequence. If any preorder is made by any groups then they get their food quicker. ", " Rugby days are an exception as we are far more busy than usual but we cannot match the service on a normal day even though we get quite a few extra staff to help. ", "Our pricing and portion sizes haven't changed either. Some dishes have a thicker sauce hence looks less in quantity but that's obvious.", "I'm glad you still like our food quality which we strive to create each time and would request you to visit on a normal day and see how do we do. Thank you ", "Kind Regards "], "reviewer_pseudo": "sandrak232017", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "14"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "30", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g528819-d9974263-r733228902-Little_Mumbai-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["We have been going here more or less since they opened a few years ago. Sadly as their popularity increased, their level of service declined showing preference to new customers and not the loyal ones. This is particularly true when the rugby is on; they forget who keeps them busy when there is no sport or concert being held at the stadium.", "Over the years portion sizes have become smaller as well. The food quality is still excellent though and reasonable prices."]}
{"id_resto": "g528819-d9974263", "id_comment": "g528819-d9974263-r736025742", "resto": "Little_Mumbai", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g528819-d9974263-Reviews-Little_Mumbai-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Good but a little disappointing ", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "1 January 2020", "answer_text": ["Dear Karanss, thank you for your review and we are sorry that you felt rushed but we already had the table booked and you said you will be gone in an hour. ", "The saag is prepared medium with kadhai masala hence it's not mild unless asked. ", "We didn't have the time to serve you another course as we would have delayed the booked table. We already had a table not finish on time and the guests left as they were not prepared to wait.", "It was new years eve and we were extremely busy. I hope you understand and give us another chance to serve you. Thank you ", "Kind Regards "], "reviewer_pseudo": "karanss", "reviewer_origin": ["Walton-On-Thames, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "292"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "105"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g528819-d9974263-r736025742-Little_Mumbai-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Went for the meal on New Year\u2019s Eve. We arrived at 6:00 and they accommodated us but told us that they needed the table by 7:30 which was fine. We wanted to order the veg sharing platter, two sides and naans. However we were disappointed to be told that we must order a main dish. Nowhere on the menu it is stated that this is the case. So we went for a single starter a main, side dish and naans. From a monetary point of view they lost out. Even though tha sag is highlighted as mild, and we specified mild, the sag was very hot. When we finished our meal at 7:05, our bill was delivered to the table without being offered desert or tea or coffee. "]}
{"id_resto": "g528819-d9974263", "id_comment": "g528819-d9974263-r740940295", "resto": "Little_Mumbai", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g528819-d9974263-Reviews-Little_Mumbai-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "One of the best Indian restaurants in London. Probably the best value.", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "24 January 2020", "answer_text": ["Dear Guest, thank you so much for your fantastic review. We are so glad you took time out to write this extensive review. ", " It really makes us feel chuffed and coming from a person who understands Indian food so well is really really great. ", " We don't have a paid account so we receive less reviews but nevertheless we appreciate everyone for their time. ", "We are a Mumbai restaurant and try to portray the best it has to offer. Hope to see you very soon. Thank you ", "Kind Regards "], "reviewer_pseudo": "Sam_sethna", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "19"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "5"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g528819-d9974263-r740940295-Little_Mumbai-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["I am writing from the perspective of an Indian living in London and Mumbai.", "Authenticity is important to me, and so I find most 'Indian' (or should I say Bangladeshi?) restaurants in the UK are an insult to Indians and Indian cuisine. There is so much wrong with these places that I don't know where to start. These places purport to offer food which is \"Punjabi\" or \"Tandoori\" which is the north Indian cuisine. It is nothing of the sort. I should know, I was born and lived in Amritsar, and this annoys me.", "Therefore, like any self-respecting Indian, I don't generally go to 'Indian' restaurants in London and prefer to cook at home, where the labour is rewarded with the aforementioned authenticity. ", "The exceptions to this (sometimes) are south Indian restaurants who's cuisine has escaped the Bangladeshi grip, or else some 'fine dining' places uptown where you will get good food, but served in a European fashion in very small portions with Michelin star attached. I often feel I could have stayed at home, served my own food on a smaller plate, and set my wallet on fire instead. Therefore my Indian 'fine dining' exploits are rare, mostly because I don't like venturing into the West End just for dinner, but also because I have run out of organs to sell.", "Going to Southall, Tooting or Hounslow is also not an option for me. These places can offer decent food, but the rest of the experience makes you want to just eat and leave.", "Enter Little Mumbai which is an antidote to this. We want something which is cheap enough to visit often without having to sell our children. We want something honest, true to the flavours of India, and smart. But not too smart; I don\u2019t enjoy myself properly when visiting places where others have dressed up to go out. ", "As its name suggests, it\u2019s not Punjabi, but the Punjabi staples are all present and correct. It offers this alongside Bombay street food, which is something most curry lovers won\u2019t recognise. It\u2019s hot, sweet, tangy, and sour all at the same time, and I fell in love with the excellent Chowpatty Platter which is a medley of four classic street favourites. The simple Pani Pooris are also brilliantly executed. These can be followed by all things recognisable to the curry lover, but delivered with finesse which puts some of the uptown expensive joints to shame.", "The service is excellent. The wines are excellent and affordable. The prices make it worth visiting often.", "This place is not for the curry lover who has adapted to the English influenced Ago-Bangla nonsense pedalled in practically every other suburb of the United Kingdom. It's for those who want to be reminded of India, or those who want to be enlightened.", "I was tempted not to write this review, since I rather like keeping this place a secret, but I would be doing humanity a disservice. We need more restaurants like this in London."]}
{"id_resto": "g528819-d9974263", "id_comment": "g528819-d9974263-r737783443", "resto": "Little_Mumbai", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g528819-d9974263-Reviews-Little_Mumbai-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Let Down on New Year's Eve", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "8 January 2020", "answer_text": ["Dear Barbara M, we are really sorry you didn't get the table on time but please do not distort the facts. Your friend initially booked the table at 8.30pm and she had asked for a specific table. That table was booked by another guest before that but when your friend asked the booking to be amended to 8pm, we asked the other party if they can finish by then and they said yes, hence we accepted your friend's request. ", "Your party turned up at precisely 7.48pm as per the CCTV and not 8.15pm as you mentioned and the table was not ready. We could have offered you another table but your friend had asked specifically for that table.", "We were extremely busy and i was in the kitchen and hence my staff requested you to wait or come after a few minutes but you left.", "We called you when the table was ready but there was no answer. It was not in our hands as the previous guests didn't leave on time. All you had to do was wait a few minutes but you preferred to walk away and write a 'let down' review. There's no question of 'rubbish service' as we didn't serve you.", "We had refused a few tables that evening but eventually had that table empty as you didn't come. Which restaurant deliberately keep themselves unoccupied that too on a new year's eve.", "We try to please everyone but sometimes it's not in our hands and people don't understand. You can only have a pleasant experience if you want to enjoy. ", "Thank you "], "reviewer_pseudo": "Barbara M", "reviewer_origin": ["Teddington, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "52"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "28"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g528819-d9974263-r737783443-Little_Mumbai-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["5 friends of mine and I went to this restaurant on New Year's Eve. One of my friends had booked and reconfirmed that morning. When we got there at 8.15 pm there was no table for us and although my friend knew the name of the man who had taken the booking, he would not come out of the kitchen to talk to her. Rubbish service. Disgraceful. We would never go back."]}
{"id_resto": "g528819-d9974263", "id_comment": "g528819-d9974263-r745208633", "resto": "Little_Mumbai", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g528819-d9974263-Reviews-Little_Mumbai-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Valentines evening 2020", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "15 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "180Lesley", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "10"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "8"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g528819-d9974263-r745208633-Little_Mumbai-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["We hadn't booked in advance, wrong move by my husband, so we went to a local pub and the restaurant called us when a table became free,excellent customer service before we had even gone into the restaurant. it had been highly recommended to my husband by friends now I would like to recommend it but try and book first.The food, my Prosecco and friendly and helpful service means I have no hesutation recommending this restaurant.I had the best butter chicken ever. The staff were so friendly and all our food arrived in good time.Give it a go you will not be disappointed."]}
{"id_resto": "g528819-d9974263", "id_comment": "g528819-d9974263-r745231845", "resto": "Little_Mumbai", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g528819-d9974263-Reviews-Little_Mumbai-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Amazing food, amazing service, moderate prices - a must visit!", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "15 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "325JamesH325", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "11"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g528819-d9974263-r745231845-Little_Mumbai-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["This is a place I can visit often. I have done now, a few times since my initial visit.", "I took a punt on this place when I had some business associates visiting from Mumbai. I thought it might be interesting (or even funny?) for them to critique what 'Mumbai' offerings were available in London.", "I was rather expecting them to be critical at least, but it transpired they were rather impressed!", "I thought the food was nothing short of exceptional. The Indian visitors with me thought the same - as if they were in a smart restaurant in uptown Mumbai. They haven't stopped singing its praises!", "The only problem with this place is that it gets VERY busy at the weekends. Booking is a must - otherwise get in early before the crowds come, or even better, come on the less well attended days earlier in the week like I have done.", "Although the place is small, it's very accommodating and the service is nice, with everything explained really well.", "The wines on offer are exceptional and not overpriced. You could easily pay double elsewhere for some of the finer white french wines.", "Best of all, the whole 'experience' is very pleasing in a way you don't get in the smart London Michelin places, with the added benefit that your wallet will thank you.", "I could easily take business colleagues here, or a date, or even on my own, and always be impressed.", "From reading other recent reviews, it seems that the only problem people have with this place is they can't get in!! Rather funny to complain of this :)", "Well done for bringing Mumbai to Twickenham!"]}
