{"id_resto": "g528819-d9974263", "id_comment": "g528819-d9974263-r745236370", "resto": "Little_Mumbai", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g528819-d9974263-Reviews-Little_Mumbai-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Now our regular favourite Indian restaurant - excellent food, service and ambience", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "15 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "227sarav", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g528819-d9974263-r745236370-Little_Mumbai-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["I'm not one for writing reviews, but this one deserves to be written.", "I'm also not keen on Indian restaurants, since my boyfriend is of Indian origin, and he cooks Indian really well. I'm therefore mostly disappointed with Indian restaurants in general.", "Although my boyfriend cooks really well, he leaves an awful mess in the kitchen - he just about uses every pan and implement possible, and there is stuff splattered everywhere when he's finished.", "On nights when I don't want to spend hours clearing up after him, we come here. It's our secret Indian restaurant. Although, these days it's not so secret and we need to book ahead on busy days.", "The food in this place is outstanding. My favourites are Paneer Shashlik, Palak Paneer, any daal (both tarka or makhani) and the Onion Bajis, which are completely different to those you would find elsewhere - perfectly crisp and tender, and not oily in the slightest. The rice is cooked to perfection. The breads are amazing, and our favourite is the Lacha Paratha. All washed down with a bottle of very affordable Gavi!!", "This place is not for those who like the aberration of Indian cuisine that has evolved to pander to the English palate. This is for those who want the real deal.", "It's a home from home, and this review has been overdue a long time!"]}
