{"id_resto": "g7377416-d10062307", "id_comment": "g7377416-d10062307-r741976323", "resto": "Albany_Spice", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g7377416-d10062307-Reviews-Albany_Spice-Brentford_Ealing_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Albany Spice is devoted to food.", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "29 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "paulsB6871TR", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "15"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "4"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g7377416-d10062307-r741976323-Albany_Spice-Brentford_Ealing_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["I live in the USA and get into London on business several times per year. I am always keen on a good Indian meal locally when I am here. Brick lane which has become too commercialized, is also an hour plus away, so I decided on the local.", "This was my second visit which I undertook in order to make sure that my first impressions were borne out. I really enjoyed my first visit and was equally as impressed the second time. Albany Spice is an unlicensed restaurant so if you want alcohol with your meal, you need to pop next door to the off-license. They will very kindly provide you with glasses at no cost.", "This allows them to concentrate on the prime function of a restaurant, which is top class food. The Peshwari chicken which they recommended and cooked for me without onions (my pet hate in any dish) was just the perfect blend of spice and flavour. I could not have asked for anything more delicious. Definitely a third and more coming."]}
