{"id_resto": "g504169-d2317000", "id_comment": "g504169-d2317000-r740069842", "resto": "Le_Petit_Nantais", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g504169-d2317000-Reviews-Le_Petit_Nantais-East_Molesey_Molesey_Surrey_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Hit and Miss", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "19 January 2020", "answer_text": ["Thank you for your feedback, let me firstly assure you that nothing you were served was leftover from Sunday as we are closed on Monday and Tuesday lunch and from our records I think you came on a Thursday lunchtime. Our sincerest apologies if you felt that the poulet chasseur was not to your taste, but it is very popular normally. We have spoken to everyone that worked that day and it would appear that you felt the portions were too big, so we are slightly confused by your comments. However please be assured of our best intentions at all times and hope to see you again "], "reviewer_pseudo": "873geraldinel", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["20", "40", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g504169-d2317000-r740069842-Le_Petit_Nantais-East_Molesey_Molesey_Surrey_England.html", "content": ["Lunch for two. Very attentive service. Nice foie gras cut from a block and a roquefort salad with way to much cheese for starters but two horrible chicken chasseurs followed with a hint of a burnt flavour. Not a good dish at all, looked unappetising too. Maybe leftover from Sunday as this was Monday lunch?"]}
