{"id_resto": "g1439404-d8445369", "id_comment": "g1439404-d8445369-r689577891", "resto": "Carved", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1439404-d8445369-Reviews-Carved-Bexleyheath_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Food fail Friday ", "diner_date": " July 2019", "rating_date": "14 July 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "975jeromeh", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "27"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "15"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1439404-d8445369-r689577891-Carved-Bexleyheath_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["I have been a customer here a few times and experiences have been let\u2019s say very mixed. ", "So after being greeted and sat invited to make our choices from the fairly short menu.", "We were told one of our selections (burger) was not available. Nor was the hot dog (two down) we settled for an alternative. Observing another set of customers leaving because their choices were not available (different to ours).", "Fortunately the staff were not too bothered we were handed our bill before our drinks were finished and then chased away with a swiftly wielded card machine. ", "Sad to say this place has had its day was once a really good diner now just going through the fast food motions."]}
{"id_resto": "g1439404-d8445369", "id_comment": "g1439404-d8445369-r738505322", "resto": "Carved", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1439404-d8445369-Reviews-Carved-Bexleyheath_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Embarrassingly poor", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "11 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "JamesWeegie91", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "5"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "5"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1439404-d8445369-r738505322-Carved-Bexleyheath_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Used to be a massive fan of Carved when it first opened and was a regular visitor with friends.", "Sad to say the days of it being a decent dinner option are long gone, however.", "When you\u2019re lucky enough to be served past 8pm, the menu is always depleted and the likelihood of your entire party being served their desired food is virtually nil.", "This, combined with prices constantly increasing commensurately with general standards going the opposite way, lead me to decide that I won\u2019t be going back.", "I was even prepared to overlook being encouraged to drink up quickly on a previous visit, despite my beer being poured only minutes prior. But my last visit was the final straw. ", "Plenty of other options more worthy of my custom going forward."]}
{"id_resto": "g1439404-d8445369", "id_comment": "g1439404-d8445369-r729657149", "resto": "Carved", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1439404-d8445369-Reviews-Carved-Bexleyheath_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Time to wax lyrical about Carved...", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "29 November 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "THEBiSHOPv2", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1439404-d8445369-r729657149-Carved-Bexleyheath_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["I\u2019ve been eating at Carved whenever I get the time ever since it opened and it\u2019s always the best. I always say to myself when I eat there \u201cwhy don\u2019t I come here more often?\u201d Compounded by the fact I\u2019m a big NFL fan. The food is epic. Simple as that. Proper American food done very very well (I personally think \u201cAmerican\u201d food is done poorly in the U.K. Like I never enjoy Bodeans when I eat there as an example.) The service is always top notch. Friendly staff that clearly care about the experience their patrons are having. Everyone seems to enjoy working there! Chatty and happy. Drinks are great. I remember when they didn\u2019t have any draught beer! That was a big upgrade in my opinion. A mix of classic and classic with a twist cocktails are done well also. If Gordon Ramsey ate at Carved, he would say the food/drinks/overall brand is executed brilliantly 100%. I\u2019m no chef or restaurateur but I think Carved is so Franchiseable. Recommendation for patrons: O.G burger with a Camden Hells. Advice to Carved: Fish tacos all year round.", "Ps. Can you get Deliveroo on the blower and extend your delivery radius by a couple of miles? (Or just open your next shop in Eltham!)"]}
