{"id_resto": "g503784-d4553810", "id_comment": "g503784-d4553810-r746641765", "resto": "Riennas", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g503784-d4553810-Reviews-Riennas-Hornchurch_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Very poor management", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "22 February 2020", "answer_text": ["Dear Toni ", "Appreciate you took some time to write this review but it would have been nicer if it had been more accurate. ", "We did apologise about the misunderstanding that had occurred in every way we could and we made sure the whole evening you could have a nice enjoyable dinner . ", "As long as a table of two became available we also offered to give that too you, to which you said no. ", "When we brought the bill over you said that you didn\u2019t want to pay the bill to it\u2019s full amount without any reasons and also pretended to be given some more drinks on the house which I don\u2019t think it was fair to do as we had previously done so to apologise, but we still gave them to you to end the evening in a nice way but in a very patronising way you asked for more. ", "I did apologise cause two \u00a35 notes had stick together so it seemed as the bill was short of \u00a310 but your response was not appropriate at all. ", "For you to assume that I brought the bill over just for the tip is absolutely wrong, and disrespectful. Our work ethic is really strong and we do not expect anything else but kind words and appreciation from our customers. ", "On the contrary your behaviour was not correct at all, especially throwing money at people is not something we are keen to accept in any situation. ", "Best regards ", "The management "], "reviewer_pseudo": "Tony C", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "6"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "4"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g503784-d4553810-r746641765-Riennas-Hornchurch_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["I called to book this restaurant on the 12th February for 6 people to attend on the 21st February. Made the booking and had heard good things about the restaurant.", "Last night upon our arrival my wife and i were informed by the manageress that she had no idea about the booking and that the restaurant was booked out. After some tooing and frowing we were offered a drink on the house but our party of six would have to share a table for four. Being a friday night and with very few options open to us we agreed and sat down.", "It felt a little like being a school kid sitting in the farthest corner of the restaurant and squeezed into a tiny space but we accepted that there had been a breakdown of communication between the person who booked us in and the manageress.", "The food was very good and we all enjoyed our meal.", "I would point out that at no time did anyone come into the restaurant to claim the table we had been sat at and i feel now that it was a ruse perpetrated by the manageress to get us to share a table for four between six people.", "The evening went well freinds of 50 years enjoying a rare night out together.", "The bill was presented and we put the relevant amount together and duly paid for our night.", "After a few minutes the manageress came over in order to inform us that the payment was 5 pence short.", "I could not believe my ears we had just parted with \u00a3360.00 for the priveledge of sitting squashed together at a table for four after making our booking 9 days ago and here she was making an issue of 5 pence.", "After some discussion it transpired that she thought we hadnt tipped and i can only assume her intention was to embarrass us into to tipping.", "Had she counted the money properly she would have known that we did indeed tip as my wife ponited out to her and counted out the money in front of her.", "When did it become ok for restaurant staff to think it,s ok to embarrass their customers in such a way.", "We would have been well within our rights to not leave a tip after the restaurant failing to make our booking and sitting 6 of us at a table for four people.", "I am appalled at the behaviour of the manageress in this restaurant."]}
