{"id_resto": "g186338-d11905307", "id_comment": "g186338-d11905307-r735113040", "resto": "Sidi_Bou_London", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d11905307-Reviews-Sidi_Bou_London-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Amazing and awesome", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "28 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "djomaab", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "3"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d11905307-r735113040-Sidi_Bou_London-London_England.html", "content": ["Amazing and awesome Tunisian food! Great atmosphere and people! Feeling home like in Tunisia! It\u2019s like a trip in Tunisia "]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d11905307", "id_comment": "g186338-d11905307-r726840368", "resto": "Sidi_Bou_London", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d11905307-Reviews-Sidi_Bou_London-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "The best of Tunisian", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "16 November 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "andrewf15421", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "16"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d11905307-r726840368-Sidi_Bou_London-London_England.html", "content": ["We were recommended this restaurant by our son who wanted to go there to celebrate his birthday. We can see why as although this restaurant is seemingly a distance away it is a short walk from Ealing Broadway Station but much more importantly the food was spectacularly good and the service clearly family run and individual. I have eaten brick in many restaurants in the Middle East but I\u2019ve never tasted such a delicately cooked and delicious version of this meal. There was a large selection but everything was home-cooked and tasty. We will definitely be going back and highly recommend this for anyone who wants to try the best of Tunisian food."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d11905307", "id_comment": "g186338-d11905307-r740313163", "resto": "Sidi_Bou_London", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d11905307-Reviews-Sidi_Bou_London-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Lovely restaurant, lovely people", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "20 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "T2272IMtomf", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d11905307-r740313163-Sidi_Bou_London-London_England.html", "content": ["Went with a couple of friends late on a Monday night - I'd been meaning to go for a long time but had never popped in. The welcome was wonderful, the food was excellent - have the breek, have the meze, have the couscous! - and we're all looking to go back for shakshuka one weekend lunchtime! We're lucky to have it in Ealing, drop in as soon as you can!"]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d11905307", "id_comment": "g186338-d11905307-r732419805", "resto": "Sidi_Bou_London", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d11905307-Reviews-Sidi_Bou_London-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "A cosy and quite surprisingly good restaurant with superlative Tunisian food.", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "13 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "241saraha", "reviewer_origin": ["London"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "8"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d11905307-r732419805-Sidi_Bou_London-London_England.html", "content": ["I went to Sidi Bou because passing through Ealing for a work commitment, I thought I would stop over and try the food. I'd heard about it as it was one of the winning entries in this year's Ealing Restaurant Awards. And Oh my, was I pleasantly surprised.", "Thoroughly earthy - and apparently the only Tunisian restaurant in the UK - you can feel the beaty and culture of Tunisia as you walk through the foor with all the decor and eye-catching pieces of earthenware and artefacts they have on display.", "I was on my own on this cold and rainy evening so settled for a light and crispy Breek A L'Oeuf - a delicious, crispy pancake made of filo pastry with herbs and filled with a fried egg. Sprinkled over with lemon juice, it was gorgeous. ", "I followed this with a hearty stew - Jilbana, filled with peas, artichoke, parsley and chunks of lamb. Scooped up with bread, it was filling, with a slight chilli kick and just the thing for a winter's evening.Truly satisfying!", "Last but not least - came the subtly sweet Tunisian pastries and an unforgetable mint tea, which with the addition of pine nuts gave its flavour and texture.", "I really loved my meal here and would receommedn it to everyone for cooking which is not only flavoursome but earthy. By the way, it's a BYO restaurant."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d11905307", "id_comment": "g186338-d11905307-r733112401", "resto": "Sidi_Bou_London", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d11905307-Reviews-Sidi_Bou_London-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Cozy atmosphere and great food", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "16 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "290monae", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d11905307-r733112401-Sidi_Bou_London-London_England.html", "content": ["The restaurant is small and friendly, and the food is superb. I've been three times now, each with different people, and everyone has been impressed and hoping to return. (But only I live close enough to keep visiting.) Although they don't serve alcohol, you can bring your own. And since the restaurant is so close to Ealing station, it would be convenient for people wanting to meet up with friends from elsewhere."]}
{"id_resto": "g528819-d4228317", "id_comment": "g528819-d4228317-r742587303", "resto": "The_Crown", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g528819-d4228317-Reviews-The_Crown-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Good restaurant.", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "2 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "920JaneJ920", "reviewer_origin": ["Teddington, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "410"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "149"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "40", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g528819-d4228317-r742587303-The_Crown-Twickenham_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["We ate here on a Thursday night in early January, and both the bar and the restaurant were busy, so a nice atmosphere.", "The restaurant is a very comfortable room, it feels like you are in someones rather grand house, there was a lovely fire going. (Tip, if eating in restaurant I would ask to be in the main part of restaurant, as the space in between bar and restaurant is a walk through so lacks privacy).", "Staff were a bit haphazard but nice; specials were read from a bit of paper, some slow service on the wine.", "The food was mixed, some was very good, other things just fine. The Mushroom tart and The Keralan vegetable curry got the thumbs up. The menu does seem to change. I really enjoyed the wine we had: Viognier, Domaine de Pennautier, Pays d\u2019Oc, France.", "I would go back and I would recommend, not a gourmet night out but good solid food in a nice setting."]}
