{"id_resto": "g680220-d1342940", "id_comment": "g680220-d1342940-r747307395", "resto": "Indian_Zest", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g680220-d1342940-Reviews-Indian_Zest-Sunbury_Surrey_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Mixed Bag", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "24 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Danny F", "reviewer_origin": ["Warwick, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "124"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "30"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g680220-d1342940-r747307395-Indian_Zest-Sunbury_Surrey_England.html", "content": ["So... where to start. My lamb curry was very good. Not as spicy as advertised, but tasty, well presented (as was everything), and generous quantities. All pretty expensive but then I'm from the Midlands. ", "Now my partner's meal. Turned up lukewarm. No rice. Curry came back... still no rice. Asked for a third time and it finally arrived (I'd suggest at least 15 mins later) once everybody else had practically finished", "A king prawn main turned up barely warm, again missing the rice as ordered. Prawns were practically inedible", "Received apologies and offers of drinks or desserts, but now it was late and those of us who had been served an edible meal plus sundries were full up", "No charge for the prawns but as you can appreciate the whole experience was disappointing "]}
