{"id_resto": "g1934185-d8861576", "id_comment": "g1934185-d8861576-r724900501", "resto": "Masala_Dabbas", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1934185-d8861576-Reviews-Masala_Dabbas-Orpington_Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Authentic Indian food", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "8 November 2019", "answer_text": ["Thank you for your feedback and we are delighted that you enjoyed your experience at MasalaDabbas. We look forward to welcoming you again. "], "reviewer_pseudo": "SirCLondon", "reviewer_origin": ["Orpington, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "85"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "63"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1934185-d8861576-r724900501-Masala_Dabbas-Orpington_Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Early evening on a Thursday and we were glad we had booked, it was busier than you'd expect. Soon found out why - great chaat, a fantastic dal makhani, an interesting and delicious lamb dish I'd never heard of before. An extremely good vegan and vegetarian selection. Charming staff, a decent and reasonably priced wine list and a most pleasant chat with the owner; one can't ask for more. I can see us becoming regulars here. Highly recommended."]}
{"id_resto": "g1934185-d8861576", "id_comment": "g1934185-d8861576-r720429111", "resto": "Masala_Dabbas", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1934185-d8861576-Reviews-Masala_Dabbas-Orpington_Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "1", "title": "Racist manager/owner", "diner_date": " July 2019", "rating_date": "22 October 2019", "answer_text": ["Thank you for your review - I am surprised how easily you brand us racists without any basis, as you yourself admit in your review! ", "it is unfortunate that you saw our request to move tables as rude and being racist. If we were indeed racist, we would not have given you a table at all. At the time of your dining in our restaurant, there were another Indian family also dining who were very happy with the way they were treated. ", "You actually had 2 children - a 2 year old and an infant. We didn't want to be rude and embarrass you so didn't tell you the real reason for asking you to move, which is that your 2 year old was banging on the table with the cutlery and the plate and not only was he at risk of injuring himself but was creating a major disturbance for the other diners in the restaurant. He also went to the table behind you and was doing the same when there were 4 diners at that table. These diners were about to complain to us and were signalling us when the manager came and suggested that you move to a table away from these diners. At this time only the two of you and your children were at the table and your friends joined you only around 8:30 PM having made a booking for 8:00 PM. If I remember correctly, I even came and told you to not allow the child to play with Knifes and plates due to the risk of injury. ", "Unfortunately, even after moving tables, your infant son kept bawling at the top of his voice and and created a very noisy atmosphere and spoiled the enjoyment of the other dines in the restaurant, who are entitled to enjoy their weekend dinner with friends in a pleasant environment. ", "The 4 people who later occupied the table you vacated were in fact walk-ins and we had no knowledge that they were coming. So it is not true that we asked you to move to accommodate 'White Diners'. ", "Unlike a number of restaurants that serve families with young children only early in the evening, we try to be child friendly and give tables for families with young children even for the late sitting. It is not unreasonable to expect the children to be reasonably well behaved and not cause a disturbance for other diners. ", "As for your other comments about the food, we endeavour to serve the highest quality food with consistent flavours which is appreciated by our guests. If you could be specific about what didn't meet your taste, we could make the necessary adjustments. As for service, the staff served you with the same care as they always do. ", "Although you have said that you would not visit our restaurant again, we do hope that you change your mind. We would be pleased to serve you with the same level of enthusiasm as we do others. I would respectfully suggest that an early booking would be more conducive when dining with very young children and infants. "], "reviewer_pseudo": "OnAir759276", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "10", "30"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1934185-d8861576-r720429111-Masala_Dabbas-Orpington_Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["I have visited this resturant a few times since it first opened on the high street. It was pretty decent the first few times and went a bit downhill as years went by. Nevertheless, it was the closest and as we had a 2 year old in our group, did not want to venture far. There were 6 (including the 2 year old) of us and we had booked in advance. We went into the restaurant and were seated by a staff member. We were looking through the menu when the big guy with glasses (who I think is one of the owners) came by and rudely asked us to get up. We were surprised and my husband questioned the need for this, he very abruptly said that he will move the table to a corner as he wanted to rearrange the seating so that he can include seating for 2 people, where we were sitting. We were confused as there was clearly a 2 seater at the corner- but no he wanted the 6 of us to get up so that he can rearrange the table for the white couple (obviously this wasnt mentioned, but we noticed this after we ordered when the couple walked in) who would be coming in soon. We should have got up and left at that moment but the staff member who sat us initially was very apologetic and we ordered. We spend close to 100 pounds in the evening and even paid service charge. I was reluctant but my husband said he would rather pay as that goes to the staff (hopefully!) and he wouldnt fault the staff. The food was mediocre but nothing to complain. It was the whole experience of being ask to rudely get up and move for a white couple, after we had sat down and made ourselves comfortable, that sullied the experience. This was when there was a perfectly good spot for a couple seat at the corner. Furthermore, being racist and rude does not help. We are frequent restaurant goers but we wouldnt be darkening their doors again. I would recommend Mumbai Central at Polhill for excellent service and much better quality food for the same price."]}
{"id_resto": "g1934185-d8861576", "id_comment": "g1934185-d8861576-r731728460", "resto": "Masala_Dabbas", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1934185-d8861576-Reviews-Masala_Dabbas-Orpington_Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Great Personliazed Hospitality", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "9 December 2019", "answer_text": ["Thank you so much for your feedback.Glad you enjoyed our food and ambience. We look forward to welcoming you again "], "reviewer_pseudo": "dlnrao1954", "reviewer_origin": ["Bhopal, India"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "9"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1934185-d8861576-r731728460-Masala_Dabbas-Orpington_Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Very warm, cosy place right on the high street. Great hosts, personalized service. Had the best Vegetable Manchurian ever with such delectable flavours and light seasoning. Served lovingly by Kiran. Great range of food options for eating and take-aways too. Huge range in the Bar. ", "Lovely decor of pictures and paintings of Indain villages and such great ambience. So clean and decor so tastefully done and welcoming to the senses. Will go there again."]}
{"id_resto": "g1934185-d8861576", "id_comment": "g1934185-d8861576-r721338441", "resto": "Masala_Dabbas", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1934185-d8861576-Reviews-Masala_Dabbas-Orpington_Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Brilliant restaurant", "diner_date": " October 2019", "rating_date": "25 October 2019", "answer_text": ["Thank you so much for your feedback and we are delighted that we could meet your dietary requirements. Looking forward to seeing you again. "], "reviewer_pseudo": "Vegan-aimee", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1934185-d8861576-r721338441-Masala_Dabbas-Orpington_Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Absolutely loved my visit, we\u2019re a big family with different dietary requirements.everyone was very knowledgeable and helpful. Two of the children had chicken tikka masala which wasn\u2019t on the menu, the chef was very flexible. The vegan platter was top class. Difficult to find a fault.amazing restaurant."]}
{"id_resto": "g1934185-d8861576", "id_comment": "g1934185-d8861576-r734063525", "resto": "Masala_Dabbas", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1934185-d8861576-Reviews-Masala_Dabbas-Orpington_Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "True Indian Food", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "22 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Traveller34335", "reviewer_origin": ["Jupiter, Florida"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "46"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "30"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1934185-d8861576-r734063525-Masala_Dabbas-Orpington_Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Having spent 4 months in Vizag (Southern India) I know what real Indian food is. This place did not disappoint. Service was great but the food was so authentic. Nice thin Naan Bread and not the thick doughy stuff that your typical English-she-fied Indian serves up. If you want to try Indian food as they eat it in India, then dont pass this place by. "]}
{"id_resto": "g1934185-d8861576", "id_comment": "g1934185-d8861576-r737372651", "resto": "Masala_Dabbas", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1934185-d8861576-Reviews-Masala_Dabbas-Orpington_Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Good in parts", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "6 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "MrsGoodfood", "reviewer_origin": ["Perth, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1934185-d8861576-r737372651-Masala_Dabbas-Orpington_Bromley_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["We went as a special treat for our (vegan) daughters Birthday.The four different starters we had went from very good - jal jeera explosion, Aloo Tikka Chat, and the soft shell crab (sadly served on a very tired supermarket-bag type of salad, where I found dark slimy bits of rotting leaves) to excellent - the scallops and the Aloo Tikka Chat. ", "The mains were all disappointing. The Chettinadu Vattu Duck- the meat was lightly cooked and pink and looked good, but sadly encased in itough rubbery skin, which totally spoiled my eating experience- it was so tough it was hard to even cut.. It was served, without garnish, on an inadequate pool of tasteless sauce - No distinction, bland. I have since had a Chettinadu curry from Marks & Spencer, which was superior) Due to the tiny amount of sauce served, I was unable, due to the dryness, to eat more than a smalI piece of the aloo stuffed nan I had ordered to accompany it. I found the nan to be amazingly good, I wish now I had just ordered the Naan and not the expensive Duck! All sadly disappointing. My partners fish (Maacher Jhol was good, and he managed my Naan with it. Daughter tried to order a couple of things from the Vegan menu, but the two she wanted weren\u2019t available, so she settled, with advice from the waiter, for a Rajma Masala, which was thoroughly ordinary. She found it bland and unexciting and very similar to tinned re-fried beans.....We would have so much appreciated something better for her birthday celebration.."]}
