{"id_resto": "g186338-d2256999", "id_comment": "g186338-d2256999-r742659915", "resto": "Pentolina", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2256999-Reviews-Pentolina-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Pasta at Pentolina", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "2 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Rob007Kent_UK", "reviewer_origin": ["Wye, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "311"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "236"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2256999-r742659915-Pentolina-London_England.html", "content": ["This beautiful rustic style Italian is tucked away behind Olympia. We had a superb lunch here on a Saturday. The linguine with fresh lobster and caramelised cherry tomatoes and the pacchen pasta with homemade sausage ragout and aged Sardinian pecorino cheese were both outstanding. Beautifully cooked and full of flavour and just the right amount of pasta. The tiramisu and the semifredo were equally good. The service was impeccable - really welcoming, courteous and attentive. This is a great little restaurant serving tasty Italian food. "]}
