{"id_resto": "g186419-d14060789", "id_comment": "g186419-d14060789-r743849531", "resto": "Enzo_s", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186419-d14060789-Reviews-Enzo_s-Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Our ex regular Italian", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "9 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "brianw875", "reviewer_origin": ["Windsor and Maidenhead, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "30"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "11"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["10", "10", "20"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186419-d14060789-r743849531-Enzo_s-Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "content": ["Took 2 friends last night to a restaurant we have always loved. Whether for a quick pizza or a 3 course meal. I have to say I was very disappointed with I hate to say this, everything. The service was not up to its usual friendliness, the food was expensive & the meatball starter although tasty was almost non existent in the bowl, it looked like something you would serve to a 5 year old. Then when mains were delivered & we realised there were no vegetables with them, it became a bit of a battle to get some as we were told the chef was closing the kitchen & wanted to go home!!!", "The final straw was all the lights went on & they opened the doors so the restaurant became very cold. it was quite clear we were wanted to go home. We hadn\u2019t even had deserts or coffee yet, it was not late before 11. So all in all a pretty poor experience. ", "If this restaurant is to survive in Windsor it has to really up its game as Windsor is a small goldfish bowl. We want be going back!!"]}
