{"id_resto": "g1752250-d14008810", "id_comment": "g1752250-d14008810-r746727483", "resto": "Masaniello_pizzeria", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1752250-d14008810-Reviews-Masaniello_pizzeria-Surbiton_Kingston_upon_Thames_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Cosy family restaurant, tasty food and friendly staff", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "22 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "VesperLyndoo7", "reviewer_origin": ["Kingston upon Thames, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "125"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "89"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1752250-d14008810-r746727483-Masaniello_pizzeria-Surbiton_Kingston_upon_Thames_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["We came recently for a dinner with a friend and our daughters as we like having girls only time. My friend suggested this restaurant which I didn't know so I was happy to try something new.", "I arrived with my daughter quite a bit earlier than the booking time as I had the time wrong but we were nevertheless welcomed and shown our table. ", "The place is compact (which I personally like a lot) and I noticed that almost all tables were occupied (always a good sign!). The toilet was clean and well maintained (another key indicator for me), and you can see how some food is prepared while you wait.", "The menu is small but has everything you may want from an authentic Italian restaurant - as my friend said, we don't like huge menus where you have to spend ages finding what you like. ", "I had the veggie ravioli which was good. I found it a bit too al dente, but that's mostly my fault as I have braces and normal food can be hard to chew. My daughter had a pizza and I helped her finish - it proved delicious and soft! ", "The staff was very friendly and helpful, always smiling and accommodating our needs.", "We will definitely come back next time we want to have a tasty Itallian home-made food. Grazie :)"]}
{"id_resto": "g504167-d14150498", "id_comment": "g504167-d14150498-r739448643", "resto": "Basil_Grape", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g504167-d14150498-Reviews-Basil_Grape-Croydon_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Excellent service, excellent food and excellent staff members", "diner_date": " June 2019", "rating_date": "16 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Annisa H", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g504167-d14150498-r739448643-Basil_Grape-Croydon_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["I went to Basil and Grape last year in June 2019. I haven't had a chance to reviee it on Tripadvisor. The service was excellent. I couldn\u2019t fault the service. As I booked my table with the waitress, I double checked again to make sure she booked it two days after, which she did. I then arrived with\u00a0 my friend that Saturday and the waitress greeted us at the door. Her name was Katie at that time (hope she still works there) and she was knowledgeable about the menu. She smiled and enjoyed herself. It's as if she really loved her job. The wine, cheese, panini and pizza, she knew everything about. On their website, it says that it has a \u201ccosy and intimate atmosphere\u201d. Well, they did keep to their words. It was cosy and intimate.\u00a0"]}
