{"id_resto": "g186338-d9711469", "id_comment": "g186338-d9711469-r738404006", "resto": "Sowa_Restaurant", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d9711469-Reviews-Sowa_Restaurant-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Cozy Restaurant", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "11 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Gotravel1881", "reviewer_origin": ["Port Dickson, Malaysia"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "21"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "4"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d9711469-r738404006-Sowa_Restaurant-London_England.html", "content": ["Had an enjoyable evening meal at the Restaurant one Saturday. I'm no connoisseur of Polish food, so I cannot vouch for its authenticity here except to say that the Pierogies and the duck dish were well cooked and delicious. Reasonably priced with good portions. Staff were attentive but not initially overly friendly. Simple deco and being a small restaurant with the tables arranged close to each other, it did not feel crowded. Recommended."]}
