{"id_resto": "g1096796-d3323113", "id_comment": "g1096796-d3323113-r741073908", "resto": "The_Oxford_Blue", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1096796-d3323113-Reviews-The_Oxford_Blue-Old_Windsor_Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Dis pairing !!!", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "25 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "melanieh988", "reviewer_origin": ["Thorpe, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "16"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "4"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1096796-d3323113-r741073908-The_Oxford_Blue-Old_Windsor_Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "content": ["My husband and I visited for our 30th Wedding Anniversary dinner .", "We were seated promptly and asked what type of water we would like . 30 minutes later the water arrived with the menus .", "Eventually a waitress returned and asked if we would like a drink and if we had decided what we would like to eat ,which was 45 minutes from being seated at the table.", "We chose the Taster menu with wine pairings or as I am now calling it dis pairing . After 10 minutes our drinks arrived but before we were less than a quarter of our way through our first drink a gin cocktail arrived which was the \u201cwine pairing \u201c for the first course . Since when has gin been classed as wine ? Regardless , we finished the cocktail but no sign of the first course then a glass of rose arrived which was for the second course !!!! No explanation was given about the pairings nor why we were now an hour and a half into our meal with no sign of the food . Next some bread arrived and finally our first course which was delicious. This carried on through every course and we had to ask if there was apairing with every course or not ( which there wasn\u2019t ) and with the dessert they served a liqueur.", "The whole evening was just chaotic ,there appeared to be no communication between the kitchen and front of house staff . If on the Taster menu it stated drinks pairing I would not have chosen this option .", "Over three hours later (most of it was waiting )we asked for the bill and presented our \u00a3150 voucher which one of our sons had given us towards the evening. The response that we received from the waitress was appalling and basically looked down her nose at us for having the audacity to give her a gift voucher bearing in mind our bill was over \u00a3300 for 2 people . The bill came and we were mortified to see that they had added a service charge , at this point I could see smoke coming out of my husbands ears . He is normally very generous but on this occasion he asked for the service charge to be removed which went down like a lead balloon and this resulted in lots of banging behind us to indicate her dissatisfaction .", "The food was delicious when it arrived and was presented beautifully but as for the rest I can honestly say the whole experience put a dampener on our anniversary"]}
{"id_resto": "g1096796-d3323113", "id_comment": "g1096796-d3323113-r741358916", "resto": "The_Oxford_Blue", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1096796-d3323113-Reviews-The_Oxford_Blue-Old_Windsor_Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Wonderful food. Terrible service!", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "26 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "435verityp", "reviewer_origin": ["Windsor and Maidenhead, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "5"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "7"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1096796-d3323113-r741358916-The_Oxford_Blue-Old_Windsor_Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "content": ["Such a shame as the food totally lived up to expectations but the service appalling! It took 4 and a half hour to have a very expensive 3 course meal. I had to keep asking for my wine to be topped up and the drinks waitress was very rude. We will not be returning which is a shame as the main course was memorable. One expects more for \u00a3400 for 4 people for lunch and the fact that they have the audacity to stick on a huge service charge is hilarious."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d4071984", "id_comment": "g186338-d4071984-r748007157", "resto": "Haweli_of_Ealing", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d4071984-Reviews-Haweli_of_Ealing-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Food heaven with a chunk of passion", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "27 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Ch1co_23", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d4071984-r748007157-Haweli_of_Ealing-London_England.html", "content": ["Now where do I start. I could not resist myself from writing this review after the mind blowing service I got from this restaurant. I Came in with my wife to be welcomed with a smile. The workers were absolutely amazing where they didn't make me feel like any old customer. My order was taken efficiently and everything on the menu was available! I was delighted with mouth watering starters which came pretty fast and when the main course came I could smell it before I even saw it come in. It was beautiful from the way it was displayed to how delicious it tasted. The meal was well cooked and the slow music in the background was extremely relaxing. I was mesmerised by how the food was cooked to perfection. They asked if the food was okay and made sure i was happy with the service given. The portion was worth what i paid and i would definitely be going back. This restaurant is a place not to be missed!! Oh and the restaurant looks stunning! Definitely an experience I will never forget thanks to the hosting and amazing food."]}
