{"id_resto": "g1096796-d3323113", "id_comment": "g1096796-d3323113-r745161026", "resto": "The_Oxford_Blue", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1096796-d3323113-Reviews-The_Oxford_Blue-Old_Windsor_Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "What a find", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "15 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "jeff s", "reviewer_origin": ["Uxbridge, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "9"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "12"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1096796-d3323113-r745161026-The_Oxford_Blue-Old_Windsor_Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "content": ["We had the four course Valentines Day lunch with a couple of nibbles beforehand. We elected not to have the optional (extra) cheese interim course as we considered there was ample food anyway.", "The website had said this was only available for evening service so we were nicely surprised as we thought this offered very good value; similar to a tasting menu.", "One driver, so we had to limit the wine and chose a very nice carafe of NZ Sauvignon.", "Everything was excellently presented and was simply delicious.", "Unfortunately, it has been a very, very long time since we ate so well in the UK.", "We had a nice (unrequested) quiet corner table which was great as it was pretty busy.", "Our service was fantastic; our waitress was a very knowledgeable and social South African.", "We did find it very strange that the water and wine glasses were plastic though.", "Would thoroughly recommend."]}
