{"id_resto": "g504175-d14866695", "id_comment": "g504175-d14866695-r740165597", "resto": "Chakra_Kingston_Riverside", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g504175-d14866695-Reviews-Chakra_Kingston_Riverside-Kingston_upon_Thames_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Simply delicious food", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "20 January 2020", "answer_text": ["Dear Diner Thank you for taking the time to review Chakra Riverside in Kingston upon Thames. Our executive chef Satya and his team take great pride in delivering the menu. Thank you for your comments which are noted. Our team lead by Sunil our GM look forward to welcoming you back soon. Kind regards"], "reviewer_pseudo": "KABReading", "reviewer_origin": ["Reading"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "123"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "95"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "40", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g504175-d14866695-r740165597-Chakra_Kingston_Riverside-Kingston_upon_Thames_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Due to previous good reviews we chose Chakra for a meal before attending a comedy night at the Rose Theatre, as we were staying at the nearby Hilton Doubletree and Chakra was very conveniently located on our walk into Kingston right on the riverfront.", "They did things slightly differently here, with a focus on quality not quantity like in some Indian restaurants. Portions were just right for us, but some may think them on the small side, but I would prefer a smaller portion of good quality food rather than a vat of slop, so it suited us down to the ground.", "The menu is not the normal phone book of 150 different dishes, but a more paired down choice of perhaps 30 main dishes, helped us as out of towners to pick from the options on offer. We chose a Chicken Gassi and a Tikka Masala with rice and nans. The Chicken Gassi was particularly delicious and my partner said the nan was superb.", "If I had to find a negative it was the slightly confused d\u00e9cor. Some was ultra-modern, but our table had French style white padded chairs with chunky green water glasses that did not go with anything else. There was also a lot of fake plants, a personal hatred of mine as they just harbour dust and germs. I think a little \u201cless is more\u201d would help. But this would not be enough to stop us coming again if we return to Kingston."]}
