{"id_resto": "g2365649-d3741279", "id_comment": "g2365649-d3741279-r727442783", "resto": "Al_Forno", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g2365649-d3741279-Reviews-Al_Forno-New_Malden_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Magnifico", "diner_date": " May 2019", "rating_date": "19 November 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "pauljeffreys", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "10"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "4"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g2365649-d3741279-r727442783-Al_Forno-New_Malden_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Nice location, perfect atmosphere, food was excellent, staff were friendly and efficient. Thoroughly excellent experience stopping here for lunch.", "My favourite moment was arriving and noticing that the chairs were hard and as I mentioned it, the waitress immediately responded by fetching a cushion for me. Very attentive and made all the difference.", "I loved it here and would recommend it. I will eat here again, without question."]}
{"id_resto": "g186338-d2257012", "id_comment": "g186338-d2257012-r732599190", "resto": "Potli_An_Indian_Market_Kitchen", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d2257012-Reviews-Potli_An_Indian_Market_Kitchen-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Charcoal Oven!!!", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "14 December 2019", "answer_text": ["Thanks very much for the amazing feedback.Look forward to seeing you again!"], "reviewer_pseudo": "soundgesture", "reviewer_origin": ["Norwich, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "600"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "166"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d2257012-r732599190-Potli_An_Indian_Market_Kitchen-London_England.html", "content": ["After walking around the area for a long time looking for the best place to eat, with the help of TripAdvisor we found this place.. On a very busy Saturday evening they found us a table. Some pappadum with delicious chutneys and a pint of cold Kingfisher we were ready to order. Service was very friendly and attentive. Decided to go for the Potli Dhaba Murgh, which is chicken on the bone, part cooked in the traditional charcoal oven then finished off in a pot with sauce and spices.. So what you get is a very tender and with the woody flavour one of the best curries I have had in the UK. The oven they use is one of the few remaining traditional ovens in London! The prices were what you would expect for the area, the service though was superb, I will be back next time in the city!! "]}
