{"id_resto": "g1646049-d2177007", "id_comment": "g1646049-d2177007-r721346445", "resto": "Martins_Place", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1646049-d2177007-Reviews-Martins_Place-Uxbridge_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Fantastic restaurant can highly recommend \ud83d\udc4d", "diner_date": " October 2019", "rating_date": "25 October 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "206melw", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "9"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "24"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1646049-d2177007-r721346445-Martins_Place-Uxbridge_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Just had a fantastic meal at Martin's this is our second visit and it never dissapoints the food is very high quality we ordered two steaks and two cordon bleu chicken dishes and all four were cooked to perfection and came with a generous helping of mixed salad,mixed vegetables and a huge dish of chips,thank you for a special meal we will be back again"]}
{"id_resto": "g1646049-d2177007", "id_comment": "g1646049-d2177007-r731578228", "resto": "Martins_Place", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1646049-d2177007-Reviews-Martins_Place-Uxbridge_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "A Great Evening!", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "9 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "HazelHolmes", "reviewer_origin": ["United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "8"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "11"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1646049-d2177007-r731578228-Martins_Place-Uxbridge_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Another great evening at Martin's. A group of ten friends met here and really enjoyed ourselves. The food was well cooked, fresh and plentiful. Thank you Martin."]}
{"id_resto": "g1646049-d2177007", "id_comment": "g1646049-d2177007-r740836953", "resto": "Martins_Place", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1646049-d2177007-Reviews-Martins_Place-Uxbridge_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "A place for food and friendship", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "23 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Dragon555x", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "140"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "91"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "40", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1646049-d2177007-r740836953-Martins_Place-Uxbridge_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["We dined here mid-week after years of not being able to get in. It is what is says it is - a friendly bistro. If you are looking for flash modern cooking, or delicate, contemporary Michelin star stuff this probably isn't for you. If you want plentiful, well-flavoured food accompanied by perfectly cooked vegetables, then you will love it.", "We ate breaded mushrooms, and onion soup to start. The mushrooms were good, the soup OK. We followed this with fillet steak with Martins own sauce (gorgeous), chicken cordon bleu (good), Calves' liver (liver lovely, not keen on the sauce) and chicken supreme (jealous of my steak). These were served with huge bowls of vegetables, all beautifully cooked.", "We finished with pancakes. I think we were expecting crepes, but these are thick pancakes, served with ice-cream and a choice of liquers. Pleasant enough.", "The food here is hearty. It is cooked to order and time goes by, but no-one notices. When not cooking, Martin comes out and puts the world to rights with his guests. A lovely man who assesses his guests well and knows how to handle them.", "Some reviews say this is old-fashioned food and I am inclined to agree. It is a bit like going back home for some proper home-cooked food. We will be back."]}
{"id_resto": "g1646049-d2177007", "id_comment": "g1646049-d2177007-r738698624", "resto": "Martins_Place", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1646049-d2177007-Reviews-Martins_Place-Uxbridge_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "It does what it says on the tin!", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "12 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "JemWW", "reviewer_origin": ["United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "42"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "19"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1646049-d2177007-r738698624-Martins_Place-Uxbridge_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["We have visited Martin's Place three times now and it simply doesn't disappoint. It is a small Bistro, run by Martin and a small crew. The food is straight from the 70's and 80's, and frankly at 80's prices. Just phenomenal value. Where else can you get Chablis, or Fillet steak, for under \u00a320? Fine dining, it is not. Brilliant, honest food, served well. Martin is a gem, a German by birth, but trained in hotels here in the UK over 30 years ago. We walked in on spec at 8, and were advised by Martin to come back at 9. We arrived at 8.45, to be greeted by Martin...\"you don't have a watch, then\" LOL. Ordering steak..Martin...\"If you had a choice, how would you like your steak cooked?\" LOL....And it was perfectly medium rare, and delicious. 2 people, 2 bottles of wine, after dinner digestive, 3 courses, all for under \u00a3100, including tip. ", "This place is a real treat for those of us who want a trip down memory lane, in an informal setting. ", "Best to book though; very small."]}
{"id_resto": "g1646049-d2177007", "id_comment": "g1646049-d2177007-r741613087", "resto": "Martins_Place", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1646049-d2177007-Reviews-Martins_Place-Uxbridge_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "A lot of hype not very good in my experience", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "27 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "vanveen37", "reviewer_origin": ["Nottingham England"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "41"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "25"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1646049-d2177007-r741613087-Martins_Place-Uxbridge_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Had pate starter some toast and pate can't really go wrong on that it was quite nice the stroganoff was very poor not great meat and a pale cream sauce dribbled over it. I only actually decided to try it because it was in the Amex Shop Small came to pay was told they don't take Amex not sure why anyone would. Enquired of Amex who are investigating as they do take Amex and why would they sign up to the Shop Small which they did if they are not going to honour it (Amex words). If the food had been good I'd not have been too bothered about the Amex issue but what I had wasn't that good anyway! Won't be returning, Wetherspoons is better! "]}
{"id_resto": "g1646049-d2177007", "id_comment": "g1646049-d2177007-r744711726", "resto": "Martins_Place", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1646049-d2177007-Reviews-Martins_Place-Uxbridge_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Great visit, amazing food", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "12 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "667maryamb", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "40", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1646049-d2177007-r744711726-Martins_Place-Uxbridge_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Had a really warm welcome from the staff, it was great because it wasn't crazy busy with loud music/people. Great place for a homely feel. The food took a little while but it was worth the wait - I had a scrumptious salmon along with veg/potatoes. Definitely an unexpected wonderland in the heart of Uxbridge."]}
{"id_resto": "g504182-d2191893", "id_comment": "g504182-d2191893-r737415582", "resto": "Casa_Nostra", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g504182-d2191893-Reviews-Casa_Nostra-Sutton_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Italian hospitality in Sutton.", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "6 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Dukedon1959", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "3"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g504182-d2191893-r737415582-Casa_Nostra-Sutton_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Lovely Italian restaurant not far from Sutton BR station.", "The food is very reasonably priced with a good cross section of dishes.", "All three of our party had pasta dishes which were tasty and served hot just as we like.I had the Casa Nostra linguine which was packed full of chicken and bacon with onions cream and peas.", "We tried a couple of the desserts which were very good also.", "All the staff were attentive and friendly. ", "I got the impression this was the type of place that people go back to time and again as many of the customers appeared to be on very friendly terms with waiters and staff."]}
