{"id_resto": "g186419-d3421328", "id_comment": "g186419-d3421328-r731178304", "resto": "Limes_of_Windsor", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186419-d3421328-Reviews-Limes_of_Windsor-Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Amazed", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "7 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "whatIthinktoday", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186419-d3421328-r731178304-Limes_of_Windsor-Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "content": ["Very impressed with the service from the staff team. They were welcoming and accommodating when meeting me and my other halfs needs during our visit. ", "Also we had afternoon tea where we could choose our own choice of filling to compared to other places in Windsor. The food was made fresh and tasted amazing. Plus if you could not finish they offer a take home box so food is not wasted", "Would 100% recommend this place for anyone looking for a lovely afternoon tea which doesnt cost an arm and leg."]}
{"id_resto": "g186419-d3421328", "id_comment": "g186419-d3421328-r723689527", "resto": "Limes_of_Windsor", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186419-d3421328-Reviews-Limes_of_Windsor-Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Hidden Gem", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "4 November 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Joanne N", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "5"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "5"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186419-d3421328-r723689527-Limes_of_Windsor-Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "content": ["I was treated to Afternoon Tea here for my birthday and it did not dissapoint. My friend booked due to the reviews she had read on here and she was right to do so. I have been to a number of afternoon teas in my time from farm shops to well known London hotels and this tea shop was one of the best up there. Freshly made food was devine and the scones were MASSIVE. We had to box up the left overs that we couldnt finish. The sandwiches were made fresh in front of us and we did ask for alternative fillings and neither of us liked coronoation chicken with no problems whatsoever. 5 stars from me and I would encourage anyone to pop in, even just for a slice of cake and cup of tea. You will not be dissapointed!"]}
