{"id_resto": "g186419-d3421328", "id_comment": "g186419-d3421328-r731234615", "resto": "Limes_of_Windsor", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186419-d3421328-Reviews-Limes_of_Windsor-Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Lovely breakfast and cake for my girlfriend's 40th!", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "7 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Lee_K_35", "reviewer_origin": ["Herne, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "7"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "5"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186419-d3421328-r731234615-Limes_of_Windsor-Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "content": ["Limes of Windsor was our first stop on our day out in Windsor for my girlfriend's 40th birthday celebrations in late November. I had pre-ordered a small birthday cake and booked a table in advance. Although I have never met Lynn (owner) I made arrangements via LOW's Facebook page and Lynn was extremely helpful. She made a delicious cake for my girlfriend which was presented after we had breakfast, and was very understanding and accommodating keeping our table available when I contacted her at short notice to say we'd be late as the M25 was a nightmare. I can understand why LOW has such good reviews. I will visit again next summer for a cuppa and another yummy sausage sandwich!"]}
