{"id_resto": "g186338-d720703", "id_comment": "g186338-d720703-r729617836", "resto": "The_Bell_Crown", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d720703-Reviews-The_Bell_Crown-London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Great atmosphere, friendly & efficient service, terrific home cooked food", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "29 November 2019", "answer_text": ["Thank you Deborah for an amazing review, and lovely comments, Hope you had a great Christmas and NY, we look forward to seeing you soon for some more Fish n Chips. XX"], "reviewer_pseudo": "25Deborah25", "reviewer_origin": ["London"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "17"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "12"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d720703-r729617836-The_Bell_Crown-London_England.html", "content": ["From the first contact to reserve a table on a busy Friday lunchtime, through to the friendly farewell, this was the perfect model of how to run a gastro pub. ", "We were greeted by name, shown to a cozy table by the fire (good acoustics), and poured over the appealing menu before settling on fish and chips. ", "It turned out to be an excellent choice - the best fish & chips I\u2019ve ever had. All piping hot - the fish was succulent and huge, the batter light and crispy, as were the chips (while also being soft on the inside), and homemade minted mushy peas. Together with homemade tartare sauce this was the perfect dish.", "We then shared the plum, pear and almond crumble which came piping hot from the oven so the crumble was nicely browned and crusty. The accompanying creme anglaise (with visible vanilla seeds) was so yummy we asked for another small jug which was brought over immediately, with a smile, and at no extra charge.", "This is a superbly run gastro pub, in an idyllic setting, where everyone takes pride in their work and the service they offer. Brilliant. "]}
{"id_resto": "g186419-d3421328", "id_comment": "g186419-d3421328-r745256446", "resto": "Limes_of_Windsor", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186419-d3421328-Reviews-Limes_of_Windsor-Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Excellent food , all baked", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "15 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "ToniC1636", "reviewer_origin": ["Slough, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "1"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186419-d3421328-r745256446-Limes_of_Windsor-Windsor_Windsor_and_Maidenhead_Berkshire_England.html", "content": ["Excellent food , all baked fresh in this delightful hidden gem . Scones were served fresh from the oven we also requested several breakfast/lunch additions that deviated from the menu . The staff were more than happy to help . Nothing was to much trouble . Would highly recommend. One of our party ordered the steak an ale pie witch is baked an shaped to cleverly look like the castle found this place to be reasonably priced as similar in the area our more expensive . Sad to see the 1 star review an strongly disagree with everything that was said . Staff are super friendly an you can see them busy baking away . As the kitchen is open planned . "]}
