{"id_resto": "g7940437-d2091217", "id_comment": "g7940437-d2091217-r745290822", "resto": "The_Pheasant_Restaurant_Pheasant_Inn", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g7940437-d2091217-Reviews-The_Pheasant_Restaurant_Pheasant_Inn-Harlington_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "3", "title": "Was not happy", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "15 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "rickyt440", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g7940437-d2091217-r745290822-The_Pheasant_Restaurant_Pheasant_Inn-Harlington_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Over all the food is really good, portions size quality very good I have not been here for over a year now but today was not happy as I felt rushed they did not give you no time at all to enjoy your meal. We ordered starters and then the main came we was only half way though our main they came again and said have you finished . Was a bit annoyed then I here one of the old lady staff member say to the manager that stupid cow don\u2019t know if she was referring to a customer or staff member but it was very unprofessional I turned around and looked at them then they went around the corner. Yet again the same lady came and said to us have you finished I felt very rushed it was like they wanted us out of there . I think they definitely need to improve for sure as there prices are not cheap after the bill came the same lady had the cheek to ask for a tip her words were don\u2019t be afraid to offer a tip what, did I just here that I looked at her considering she was not even our server. ( what a joke)"]}
{"id_resto": "g580427-d2070022", "id_comment": "g580427-d2070022-r744183638", "resto": "Ciao_Bella", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g580427-d2070022-Reviews-Ciao_Bella-Romford_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Family restaurant with decent food", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "10 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Lorelai_dR", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "30", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g580427-d2070022-r744183638-Ciao_Bella-Romford_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["We visit Ciao Bella in Romford every two or three months.", "It's a convenient, no-fuss casual independent place where you can eat with friends or family, have a fast lunch or a nice dinner for two on these evenings when you don't want to cook, would like to escape from everyday life and don't have a mood for dressing up.", "Our last visit was in January 2020.", "The food served here is simple, comforting and well made. The portions are large, the food is tasty and well presented and the prices are average. Don't expect the top quality tough.", "The menu is not too extensive but has a decent choice of dishes.", "I'm a huge fan of Calamari Fritti, a classic Italian antipasto, deep-fried, golden and crunchy, served with tartar sauce. It needs additional seasoning. Maybe not the best I ever had but very close.", "Zucchini Fritti is also very nice, you can find it in 'sides'.", "My personal favourite pasta is Linguine Gamberoni which looks beautiful, smells heavenly and tastes very well.", "If you have a chance, mussels in tomato sauce from the seasonal menu are worth trying. ", "Not all food is amazing. Caprese and Insalata Tricolore were less than impressive. Desserts are nothing worth mentioning, but coffee is great.", "The service quality is not consistent, many young servers lack experience, sometimes plates are sitting on a table too long while other time waiters try to clean up while you're still eating.", "The interior is not very stylish but as soon as the food arrives you forget about it."]}
