{"id_resto": "g504182-d4137803", "id_comment": "g504182-d4137803-r741361186", "resto": "The_Grumpy_Mole", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g504182-d4137803-Reviews-The_Grumpy_Mole-Sutton_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Saturday night out", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "26 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Robert E", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "8"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g504182-d4137803-r741361186-The_Grumpy_Mole-Sutton_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["First we have been here and have we been missing.Stunning food all courses that the four of us had were outstanding.Our friend's wife who booked the table had been here before and said is was superb she was spot on.One i have got to add the waitress Amy and her 2 colleagues Mark & James were just outstanding great sense of humor so so polite and friendly and further to this point what i noticed as we had a drink at the bar waiting for our friends to turn up as many many decades ago whilst at college in the late 70's i had a evening and weekend job at a restaurant and we had a great team atmosphere and you don't see this very often these day's where as your staff had this vibe in spades WILL BE BACK ASAP"]}
{"id_resto": "g504182-d4137803", "id_comment": "g504182-d4137803-r737070277", "resto": "The_Grumpy_Mole", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g504182-d4137803-Reviews-The_Grumpy_Mole-Sutton_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "2", "title": "Disappointing", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "5 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Gold1234567", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "20"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "6"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g504182-d4137803-r737070277-The_Grumpy_Mole-Sutton_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["I am not sure that I understand all of the fantastic reviews. We visited The Cheam Grumpy Mole on a Sunday. We had Burger and Chips and sausage and mash. Two pub staples that surely it is hard for anyone to get wrong.", "Unfortunately, the Beef in the Beef Burger tasted very much like a shop bought cheap beef patty, not nice!!! The sausages although better still had that cheap supermarket sausage. Given the price i would be expect the burgers to be homemade anyway. Overall, I would suggest that if they are to serve these simple things on the menu that they up the quality of the meat they supply. ", "It was a shame as the serving staff were very friendly and it seemed like a nice atmosphere."]}
