{"id_resto": "g504169-d12614603", "id_comment": "g504169-d12614603-r740619715", "resto": "Canela_Cafe", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g504169-d12614603-Reviews-Canela_Cafe-East_Molesey_Molesey_Surrey_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "In East Molesey on a cold day", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "22 January 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "adam l", "reviewer_origin": ["Teddington, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g504169-d12614603-r740619715-Canela_Cafe-East_Molesey_Molesey_Surrey_England.html", "content": ["On a cold day in East Molesey, planning some photography, took the precaution of fuelling up beforehand. I tried Canela, directly opposite the railway station. Interesting decor and comfortable ambience. Good choice on the menu. Service was friendly and fast, and my sausage sandwich and fresh coffee were delicious and well priced."]}
{"id_resto": "g504169-d12614603", "id_comment": "g504169-d12614603-r706004230", "resto": "Canela_Cafe", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g504169-d12614603-Reviews-Canela_Cafe-East_Molesey_Molesey_Surrey_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Great find!", "diner_date": " August 2019", "rating_date": "3 September 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Happiness479822", "reviewer_origin": ["Kingston upon Thames, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "9"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "3"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g504169-d12614603-r706004230-Canela_Cafe-East_Molesey_Molesey_Surrey_England.html", "content": ["Small and very cute restaurant. Doesn't have a huge menu, but everything I saw going out, including our food looked delicious. My smoked salmon breakfast was excellent and very reasonably priced. They were also very flexible and adapted the dishes to our preference. We'll be returning, for sure!"]}
{"id_resto": "g504169-d12614603", "id_comment": "g504169-d12614603-r707842749", "resto": "Canela_Cafe", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g504169-d12614603-Reviews-Canela_Cafe-East_Molesey_Molesey_Surrey_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Brilliant cafe with really good menu.", "diner_date": " September 2019", "rating_date": "8 September 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Jackiepcs", "reviewer_origin": ["Portsmouth, England"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "137"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "55"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g504169-d12614603-r707842749-Canela_Cafe-East_Molesey_Molesey_Surrey_England.html", "content": ["After a very long journey to get the Hampton Court maze we (one senior and one 5yr old) fell out of the railway station and crossed the road to this small but perfectly formed cafe. We were allowed to use the toilet but did order a coffee and cake and sat at a table in the window. The coffee was very good and the cake divided between us went down very smothly. I did peruse the menu with a view to coming back for a late lunch (we didn't have time unfortunately) and was delighted at the choice of english and colombian food on offer. I could have eaten my way through the menu and there is a childrens section so 2 contented diners! We will be returning soon so will leave pleanty of time for lunch then visit the maze. Don't miss this gem."]}
{"id_resto": "g504169-d12614603", "id_comment": "g504169-d12614603-r707495542", "resto": "Canela_Cafe", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g504169-d12614603-Reviews-Canela_Cafe-East_Molesey_Molesey_Surrey_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "My favourite caf\u00e9!", "diner_date": " September 2019", "rating_date": "7 September 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "cloud9leeds", "reviewer_origin": ["Leeds, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "142"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "50"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g504169-d12614603-r707495542-Canela_Cafe-East_Molesey_Molesey_Surrey_England.html", "content": ["I went here last year before the Hampton Court Car Concours and it was so good we went again. Excellent Colombian tortilla for breakfast which again was so good we came back for the equally delicious plantain dish for lunch. A bit understaffed, so don\u2019t be in a rush, but well worth the wait. Love it."]}
{"id_resto": "g7377416-d7133258", "id_comment": "g7377416-d7133258-r714501391", "resto": "The_Express_Tavern", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g7377416-d7133258-Reviews-The_Express_Tavern-Brentford_Ealing_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Very happy with our selection", "diner_date": " September 2019", "rating_date": "1 October 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "HectorVoyager", "reviewer_origin": [], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "24"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "20"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g7377416-d7133258-r714501391-The_Express_Tavern-Brentford_Ealing_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Usually when staying in Brentford we always visit our favourite Indian restaurant but this time we were with friends who are not so keen on spicy food. We opted for The Express Tavern and we certainly were not dissapointed. We all had delicious sunday roasts accompanied with fresh vegetables and the horsradish and mint sauce arrived in advance without being requested. We were all very happy and the staff who served us were charming and efficient."]}
{"id_resto": "g7377416-d7133258", "id_comment": "g7377416-d7133258-r717255486", "resto": "The_Express_Tavern", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g7377416-d7133258-Reviews-The_Express_Tavern-Brentford_Ealing_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Sunday Favourite", "diner_date": " October 2019", "rating_date": "11 October 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Greenjack72", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "13"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "5"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g7377416-d7133258-r717255486-The_Express_Tavern-Brentford_Ealing_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["The bar that has it all, great food, amazing selection of beers - lager, cider and ale (cask & keg) - a huge garden and a friendly atmosphere. Manages to provide everything the gastro-pubs do, but has retained it's individual style and feels like a genuine local. Also has a great vinyl collection that plays when the sport isn't on. Going to get busy once the stadium is finished, so get there before the rugby/soccer crowd pack it out."]}
{"id_resto": "g7377416-d7133258", "id_comment": "g7377416-d7133258-r717926654", "resto": "The_Express_Tavern", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g7377416-d7133258-Reviews-The_Express_Tavern-Brentford_Ealing_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Great atmosphere and value for money", "diner_date": " October 2019", "rating_date": "13 October 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "msox106", "reviewer_origin": ["Doncaster, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "81"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "32"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["50", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g7377416-d7133258-r717926654-The_Express_Tavern-Brentford_Ealing_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["We stopped off here to eat before going to Kew Gardens and found a really wonderful pub full of London atmosphere plus a great selection of gins :-)", "The staff were really freindly and gave great service. The menu was quite extensive and I got a free drink as it turned out to be 'ribs' day. The ambience was brilliant with lots of quirky objects and a fabulous garden.", "We were expecting to have to pay a lot being in the Richmond area so were delighted we with value for money. We will definitley be calling again next time we are in the area.", "Would thoroughly recommend a visit here."]}
{"id_resto": "g7377416-d7133258", "id_comment": "g7377416-d7133258-r735811092", "resto": "The_Express_Tavern", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g7377416-d7133258-Reviews-The_Express_Tavern-Brentford_Ealing_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Cannot comment on the food, but the beer choice and quality is usually brilliant", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "31 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Steve_of_N21", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "1628"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "986"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g7377416-d7133258-r735811092-The_Express_Tavern-Brentford_Ealing_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["The Express Tavern is my usual goto pub for a decent pint when I am in the vicinity of Kew Bridge and it rarely lets me down. I usually ensconce myself in the Chiswick bar with its ten real ale handpumps and enjoy as many as I can in the time I have allowed. You can usually rely on there being a mix of beer styles with blond and citrus beers to the fore in the summer months and dark beers available in the cold winter months as they were during my recent visit when I enjoyed a couple of good stouts.", "I hope the Brentford fans appreciate this one when it becomes one of the nearest pubs to their new ground and I really hope the Express Tavern does not change because of this."]}
{"id_resto": "g7377416-d7133258", "id_comment": "g7377416-d7133258-r744347597", "resto": "The_Express_Tavern", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g7377416-d7133258-Reviews-The_Express_Tavern-Brentford_Ealing_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "John Gallagher", "diner_date": " November 2019", "rating_date": "11 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "johngM9871EW", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "2"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g7377416-d7133258-r744347597-The_Express_Tavern-Brentford_Ealing_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["A lovely pub with a great beer garden. Staff polite and helpful. We have made a few visits in the last year and have enjoyed the beer and the meals before heading home after afternoons in Kew Gardens. Will definitely be back soon."]}
{"id_resto": "g7377416-d7133258", "id_comment": "g7377416-d7133258-r718188501", "resto": "The_Express_Tavern", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g7377416-d7133258-Reviews-The_Express_Tavern-Brentford_Ealing_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Great meal", "diner_date": " October 2019", "rating_date": "14 October 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "Cakefan", "reviewer_origin": ["Bristol"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "10"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "2"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g7377416-d7133258-r718188501-The_Express_Tavern-Brentford_Ealing_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["Great meal and brilliant service. Lovely pub that was busy and friendly. The burger and chips was fantastic as were the fish and chips, salad and squid. All the meals that came out of the kitchen looked great. Wish we lived locally and could go more often."]}
