{"id_resto": "g186338-d734325", "id_comment": "g186338-d734325-r747307904", "resto": "Restaurant_Michael_Nadra_Chiswick", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g186338-d734325-Reviews-Restaurant_Michael_Nadra_Chiswick-London_England.html", "rating": "4", "title": "Expensive but worth it", "diner_date": " February 2020", "rating_date": "24 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "notacouchpotato", "reviewer_origin": ["London, England"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "452"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "180"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["30", "40", "40"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g186338-d734325-r747307904-Restaurant_Michael_Nadra_Chiswick-London_England.html", "content": ["I was reminded by TA that the last time I reviewed this restaurant I entitled it 'disappointing and lacking in atmosphere'. well, what a difference a number of years make! This time, we found the place warm and welcoming both in the decor and from the staff. It is quite small and the tables are close together but we happily chatted to diners on both sides. The wait for service was bit extended. we decided to go for the tasting menu with matching wines (and yes, it was expensive). We were delighted with the range and variety though could have done without the two lots of dessert at the end. And we won't take years to return!"]}
