{"id_resto": "g504169-d12614603", "id_comment": "g504169-d12614603-r731352226", "resto": "Canela_Cafe", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g504169-d12614603-Reviews-Canela_Cafe-East_Molesey_Molesey_Surrey_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "A great and leisurely Sunday brunch", "diner_date": " December 2019", "rating_date": "8 December 2019", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "mbY1968GI", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "15"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "6"]], "other_ratings_category": [], "other_ratings_value": [], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g504169-d12614603-r731352226-Canela_Cafe-East_Molesey_Molesey_Surrey_England.html", "content": ["This is a great little cafe with a Colombian twist . An eclectic mix of tables & chairs gives this a cosy feel. You can\u2019t book but as it\u2019s quite inconspicuous we\u2019ve never had a problem getting a table. That said on this visit we got the last one. If it\u2019s busy and you are in a rush then this is not for you but as the sign says preparing fresh food takes time. Having said that 15 minutes with an excellent coffee is hardly a wait. ", "They allow dogs which just adds to the homely atmosphere. ", "My \u201cCooked Breakfast\u201d was excellent and something I will repeat although I was tempted by some of the other meals & snacks coming out of the kitchen. The very young staff have an excellent manner and the service is first rate. ", "This place deserves to be very popular but selfishly I hope it doesn\u2019t become too popular! "]}
