{"id_resto": "g1999999-d8306107", "id_comment": "g1999999-d8306107-r743521690", "resto": "Zufa_Restaurants", "resto_url": "/Restaurant_Review-g1999999-d8306107-Reviews-Zufa_Restaurants-Northwood_Greater_London_England.html", "rating": "5", "title": "Absolutely fantastic, tasty, well presented Lebanese Food", "diner_date": " January 2020", "rating_date": "7 February 2020", "answer_text": null, "reviewer_pseudo": "AllanG593", "reviewer_origin": ["London, United Kingdom"], "reviewer_info_sup": [["pencil-paper", "17"], ["thumbs-up-fill", "10"]], "other_ratings_category": ["Value", "Service", "Food"], "other_ratings_value": ["40", "50", "50"], "url": "https://www.tripadvisor.co.uk/ShowUserReviews-g1999999-d8306107-r743521690-Zufa_Restaurants-Northwood_Greater_London_England.html", "content": ["I have visited Zufa's restaurant 5 times to visit a friend. Joseph and George the branch managers always look after my friend Rene and I. As you first enter, the restaurant is styled very simply and elegantly. We always get a friendly reception. You can order whatever you want from the menu or lunchtime specials. The food is reasonably priced and certainly not extravangantly priced. The food is very tasty and they offer a variety of Lebanese dishes. I can recommend the Chicken shish wrap, which comes with fries and salad. We also had hummous, flat bread, pickles. Last time I had the chicken soup as I wasn't that hungry and can honestly say the flavours were home-made and tonnes of chicken. Served with flat bread it was delightful.", "I also like everything is freshly presented. I can be critical of places but the two other comments is that the salad is exceptionally fresh. Also, the toilets in the restaurant are very clean (my way of judging a restaurant lol). If you're in the area I really would recommend this place. 5 star rating it deserves."]}
